{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-other-post-js","path":"/projects/20180124-puertoricoscoresheet/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The classic board game Puerto Rico can be time consuming to score since it has\nso many ways to get points. Having heard about React from Jordan Rhea\n(<a href=\"https://github.com/rheajt\">rheajt</a> on Github), I decided to try to make a\nscoring webapp.</p>\n<p>Through the use of many tutorials, I was able to understand the design\nprinciples of React, such as components and state flow, and use them to design\nthe components and put them together. For visual design, I used Reactstrap, a\npackage based on Bootstrap, for its easy styling and layout options.</p>\n<p>The webapp proved a success with my gaming group, and spurred me on to try other\nsoftware design projects.</p>\n<p>(Header image by <a href=\"http://riograndegames.com/games.html?id=4\">Rio Grande Games</a>)</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Update</strong>: I redesigned the entire state system for the app to use Redux,\nwhich should make it easier to add in buildings from the expansion later.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Puerto Rico Scoresheet","subtitle":"Board game scoring webapp","tags":["javascript","react","redux","webapp"],"category":"Personal","linkPillTitles":["Code Repo","Demo"],"linkPillHrefs":["https://github.com/ROldford/puerto-rico-scoresheet","https://roldford.github.io/puerto-rico-scoresheet/"],"date":"24 January, 2018","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='500'%20height='250'%20viewBox='0%200%20500%20250'%20preserveAspectRatio='none'%3e%3cpath%20d='M63%2030v1c2%201%201%205-1%207v3c-2%202-1%203%202%202l3%201h2l-1-1c-1-1-2-5%200-5l3-1%201%202v4h14c2%202%204%200%203-3l1-2%202%202c0%203%202%205%203%203h7c2-3%203-4%200-7-1-1-2-1-4%202s-3%203-3%202l1-3c2%200%202%200%200-2-1-2-2-2-3%200l-4%201h-8c-1%202-2%202-3%200-1-1-1-1-